  "notes": "Primary source: RFEG club page (per-hole par, hcp, meters for 4 tees, Vc/Vs per gender). Cross-checked: The Social Golfer yellow-tee card matches RFEG hole-by-hole exactly for par, stroke index, and distances (its 'yards' column is mislabeled — values are meters, total 5673 = RFEG Amarillas). Golfshake totals in true yards (6298/6204/5703/5176) are exact conversions of RFEG meter totals (5759/5673/5215/4733) and its slopes 136/137/139 match. Verified: pars sum to 72 (front 37, back 35), stroke indexes form a permutation of 1-18, and each tee's 18 distances sum exactly to its published total. RFEG rates Blancas/Amarillas men-only; Azules and Rojas are rated for both genders (women's Vc/Vs: Azules 75.3/143, Rojas 72.4/139). Minor discrepancy: The Social Golfer lists rating 72.0/slope 129 for yellow, which differs from RFEG's 71.8/136 — RFEG values used as authoritative. Hole 5 is a short par 4 (240 m) — confirmed by both per-hole sources."
